info.headline: Flood Advisory issued July 15 at 9:40PM CDT until July 15 at 10:30PM CDT by NWS Duluth MN
info.description:
* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.
* WHERE...In Minnesota, Lake and St. Louis Counties.
* WHEN...Until 1030 PM CDT Tuesday.
* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Water over roadways. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 940 PM CDT Tuesday, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in the advisory area. Between 2 and 4 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts up to 0.5 inches are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Duluth, Two Harbors, McQuade Harbor, French River, City of Rice Lake, Stoney Point, Island Lake, Knife River, Larsmont, Pike Lake Near Duluth, Fredenberg, Lakewood Twp, North Shore, Palmers, Wild Rice Lake and Fish Lake. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction:
Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding.
Report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and to the National Weather Service in Duluth when you can do so safely. Flooding can be reported to the National Weather Service at 1-800-685-8612.
